                  <handDesc>
                  <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                  <seg type="rubrication">
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኢግዚአብሔር፡</foreign>
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማርያም፡</foreign>
                  </seg>
                  <desc>The word God is not rubricated in the first three works; the word Mary is rubricated in the final two works</desc>
                  <desc>There is no columetric layout of text</desc>
                  </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#iiv(erso)" facs="003">Fol. iiv(erso)</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1066DavidHarp">David Playing the Harp</ref> with caption <q>King Prophet David</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#11r" facs="013">Fol. 11r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1031VirginAndChild">Virgin and Child</ref></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3"><locus target="#26r" facs="028">Fol. 26r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref>,<persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4585Georgeo">St George of Lydda</persName> and the <term key="dragon" ana="#dragon"/> and Birutawit. With caption <q>“Saint George,” “Dragon.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d4"><locus target="#56r" facs="058">Fol. 56r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1091TriumphalEntry"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: AT1091TriumphalEntry</span></ref> with caption <q>“Hosanna” “Zacheus.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d5"><locus target="#75r" facs="077">Fol. 75r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1093TakingRobeofJesus">Taking off the Robe of Jesus</ref> with caption <q>“The removing of the robe of Our Lord Jesus Christ.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d6"><locus target="#101r" facs="103">Fol. 101r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1038Baptism">Baptism of Jesus</ref> with caption <q>“How John the Baptist baptized Our Lord Jesus Christ,” “River Jordan.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d7"><locus target="#126r" facs="128">Fol. 126r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1015Flagellation">Flagellation of Jesus</ref> with caption <q>“Barabas,” “The Jews” “The scourging of Our Lord Jesus Christ.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d8"><locus target="#175r" facs="177">Fol. 175r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1092SacrificeIsaac">The Sacrifice of Isaac</ref> with caption <q>“The Sacrifice of Abraham.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d9">
                    Decorative designs:
                    crude harägs in purple ink appear after every ten psalms (e.g., <locus target="#8v #17r" facs="011 019">folss. 8v, 17r, </locus>);
                    <locus target="#159r #167v #184v" facs="161 170 187">159r, 167v, 184v, </locus> (line of alternating red and black dots with full stops);
                    <locus target="#171r" facs="173">171r</locus> (multiple full stops)
                    </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <locus target="#ir(ecto)" facs="001">Fol. ir(ecto)</locus>
                    <desc type="Asmat">
                    Asmat prayer for help in learning, incomplete, written upside down
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <locus target="#iv(erso)" facs="002">Fol. iv(erso)</locus>
                    <desc type="Asmat">
                    Asmat prayer for help in learning, written upside down
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a3">
                    <locus target="#iir(ecto)" facs="002">Fol. iir(ecto)</locus>
                    <desc type="GuestText">
                    copy of <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur#Ps1"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: LIT2000Mazmur#Ps1</span></ref>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a4">
                    <locus target="#184v #185r" facs="187">Fols. 184v, 185r</locus>
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                    notes of secondary ownership, Mämhǝrä Wäldä Maryam, Qes Gäbrä Giyorgis
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a5">
                    <locus target="#185v" facs="188">Fol. 185v</locus>
                    <desc type="GuestText">
                    copy of text from a psalm in crude hand. List of select <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur">Mazmura Dāwit</ref>, written in pencil
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <locus target="#1 #10 #25 #55 #74 #100 #125 #174" facs="003 012 027 057 076 102 127 176">Fols. 1, 10, 25, 55, 74, 100, 125, 174</locus>
                    <desc>
                    yellow string is sewn into the fore edge in indicate location of illuminations; marginal notation throughout to mark readings as navigation system
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <locus target="#32r #37v #41r #54r #58r" facs="034 040 043 056 060">Fols. 32r, 37v, 41r, 54r, 58r</locus>
                    <desc>etc., words of text are written interlinearly
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <locus target="#8r #37v #87v #174r #176r" facs="010 040 090 176 178">Fols. 8r, 37v, 87v, 174r, 176r</locus>
                    <desc>etc., lines of text are written interlinearly
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                    <locus target="#21v #174r" facs="024 176">Fols. 21v, 174r</locus>
                    <desc>
                    erasure markings are visible
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e5">
                    <locus target="#27v #34v #39v #46r #58r" facs="030 037 042 048 060">Fols. 27v, 34v, 39v, 46r, 58r</locus>
                    <desc>etc., text has been removed
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e6">
                    <locus target="#8r #9r #9v #67v" facs="010 011 012 070">Fols. 8r, 9r, 9v, 67v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    This scribe has avoided the problem of lines of text too long to fit on one line by adopting an aspect ratio that leaves ample room for the width of most lines. On a few occasions, the line would have been too long and the scribe finishes the end of the line with words written smaller so as to avoid leftover text (e.g., 8r, 9r, 9v). Occasionally a line is still too long and has to be completed above or below the end of the line. (e.g., 67v)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </additions>
               </physDesc>
               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origDate when="1750">eighteenth  century</origDate>
                  </origin>
               </history>
